{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isJoinControl"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There are two scalars for which this property is ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When U+200C ZERO WIDTH NON-JOINER is inserted between two characters, it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directs the rendering engine to render them separately\/disconnected when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it might otherwise render them as a ligature. For example, a rendering","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"engine might display “fl” in English as a connected glyph; inserting the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"zero width non-joiner would force them to be rendered as disconnected","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"glyphs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When U+200D ZERO WIDTH JOINER is inserted between two characters, it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directs the rendering engine to render them as a connected glyph when it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"would otherwise render them independently. The zero width joiner is also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"used to construct complex emoji from sequences of base emoji characters.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, the various “family” emoji are encoded as sequences of man,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"woman, or child emoji that are interleaved with zero width joiners.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This property corresponds to the “Join_Control” property in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.unicode.org\/versions\/latest\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:s7UnicodeO6ScalarV10PropertiesV13isJoinControlSbvp","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"isJoinControl","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"name":"iPadOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"8.0"},{"name":"Mac Catalyst","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.10"},{"name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"9.0"},{"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"2.0"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isJoinControl","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"Swift","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Unicode","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Unicode\/Scalar","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Unicode\/Scalar\/Properties-swift.struct"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"A Boolean value indicating wh